# Enforce LF line endings in working trees on every platform.
#
# Without this, Windows checkouts use git's default core.autocrlf=true and
# convert source to CRLF. tsgo (typecheck) tolerates that, but the vitest
# esbuild transform of the CLI import chain throws "SyntaxError: Invalid or
# unexpected token" on build (windows-latest) only. Forcing LF keeps Windows
# checkouts byte-identical to Linux/macOS.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets: never normalize or diff as text.
*.png binary
*.swift text eol=lf
vendor/oracle-notifier/OracleNotifier.app/** binary
